Package: ggchameleon
Title: Hassle-Free Theming for GGplotting
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Aaron", "Graybill", , "aarongraybill12@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Automatically and consistently apply custom colors, fonts, 
    and theme elements to plots made by the 'ggplot2' package. This is useful
    for creating a cohesive 'brand' among charts that incorporates the same
    elements.
URL: https://github.com/aarongraybill/ggchameleon
BugReports: https://github.com/aarongraybill/ggchameleon/issues
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
Imports:
    curl,
    farver,
    ggplot2,
    httr,
    methods,
    rlang,
    scales,
    spacesXYZ,
    sysfonts (>= 0.8.8),
    showtext,
    yaml
Depends: 
    R (>= 2.10)
